Add platform-bus NIC support for VPP via DPDK DPAA PMD with kernel handoff.

NXP DPAA1 FMan Ethernet NICs (driver: fsl_dpa) are on the platform bus,
not PCI. At boot ALL ports (eth0-eth4) are owned by the kernel via:
  fsl_dpaa_mac  — MAC hardware control (PHY, link state)
  fsl_dpa       — Linux netdev (creates ethN)

This patch enables VPP to take ownership of selected ports when the user
configures them with 'set vpp settings interface ethX':

1. Adds fsl_dpa to SUPPORTED_DRIVERS and not_pci_drv lists
2. All VPP-configured interfaces use driver='dpdk' — DPAA PMD for fsl_dpa
   platform-bus NICs, standard DPDK for PCI NICs
3. Injects original_driver into iface_config so startup.conf.j2 can
   distinguish platform-bus from PCI NICs
4. Adds _dpaa_unbind_ifaces() that unbinds fsl_dpa from VPP-assigned
   interfaces before DPDK starts, preventing FMan FQ conflicts
   (kernel panic if both fsl_dpa and DPDK DPAA PMD control same FQ)
5. Persists unbound state to /run/vpp-dpaa-unbound.json for ExecStopPost
   rebind (see vpp.service.d/dpaa-rebind.conf added via auto-build.yml)
6. startup.conf.j2: enables dpdk_plugin.so and af_xdp_plugin.so,
   skips PCI dev entries for DPAA NICs (bus auto-discovers), adds no-pci
   when only platform-bus NICs are present
7. Lowers resource minimums for embedded ARM64 boards (2 CPUs, 256M heap)
8. Removes SSE4.2 CPU check (irrelevant on ARM64)

Port ownership lifecycle:
  boot               → all eth0-eth4 under kernel (fsl_dpa creates netdevs)
  set vpp ... eth3   → apply() unbinds eth3 from fsl_dpa, VPP/DPDK claims it
  delete vpp ... eth3→ ExecStopPost rebinds eth3 to fsl_dpa (no reboot needed)

Tested on NXP LS1046A Mono Gateway with VPP v25.10.0-48 DPAA PMD on
eth3/eth4 (10G SFP+).

